<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="354" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d354">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.51/295</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Assistant Secretary of the Treasury</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Leffingwell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Counselor
                                    for the Department of State</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Polk</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-07">
                                        <hi rend="italic">March 7, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dear Mr. Polk</hi>: The Secretary of the
                                Treasury is intending to establish a credit of $15,000,000 in favor
                                of the Republic of Cuba and I will be obliged if you will advise
                                this department whether the Republic of Cuba has power to incur this
                                indebtedness and whether the Cuban Minister has authority to sign
                                obligations for the amounts advanced. It is intended to take Cuban
                                demand obligations for the amounts advanced, secured by the pledge
                                of bonds of the Republic of Cuba authorized by the act of the
                                Congress of Cuba of July 31, 1917.</p>
                            <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">R. C. Leffingwell</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>